.TH svscanboot 8
.SH NAME
svscanboot \- starts
.BR svscan (8)
in the service directories, with output and error messages logged through
.BR readproctitle (8).

svscanboot is available in daemontools 0.75 and above.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B svscanboot
[
.I directory1 directory2 ...
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B svscanboot
(without any command-line arguments) runs svscan command

svscan /service 2>&1 

with SCANLOG defined and SCANINTERVAL set to 300 seconds.

If
.B svscanboot
is given a command-line argument, it startups up svscan for the
.I directory
given on the command line (instead of just svscan /service).

.B svscanboot
sets $PATH to

 QMAIL/bin:/usr/local/bin:/bin:/sbin:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin

(all in one line, no space)

and clears all other environment variables.

The recommended way is to put the following entry in /etc/inittab to invoke svscanboot.

SV:345:respawn:QMAIL/bin/svscanboot <>/dev/console 2<>/dev/console

(assuming that you have configured services in both /service1 and /service2)
